🃏 Full Nerts Rules & Gameplay Logic (Updated)
1. Game Basics

Uses a standard 52-card deck (no jokers).

Up to 6 players per match.

First player to reach 100+ points wins.

Cards placed into center shared stacks (A → K, same suit) = +1 point each.

When a player empties their Nerts pile and presses “NERTS!”, the round ends.

Every remaining card in the Nerts pile = −2 points.

2. Player Play Area

Each player has their own private play area consisting of:

A. Personal Deck (Draw Pile)

Contains 33 cards at the start of the round.

Clicking the deck reveals 3 cards, but:
Only the top (third) card is playable.

When the playable card is used, the next card underneath becomes available.

When the deck is exhausted, clicking cycles the used cards back.

B. Nerts Pile

A personal stack of 13 face-up cards.

Emptying this pile allows the player to click “NERTS!” to end the round.

Cards left here at round end count as −2 points.

C. Six Personal Stacks (Tableau Columns)

6 stacks, each starting with 1 card (total of 6 cards).

Stacking rules:

Must build in descending order (K → 2)

Must alternate colors (red/black)

Entire valid sequences may be moved as a unit

3. Initial Card Distribution (Corrected)

Each player receives an individually shuffled 52-card deck:

6 cards → personal stacks (1 per stack)

13 cards → Nerts pile

33 cards → personal deck

Total = 6 + 13 + 33 = 52 cards

4. Center Shared Stacks

All players may place cards here.

Cards must match suit and be placed in ascending order (A → K).

Each card placed = +1 point.
